main event: Two brightly lit objects, one above the other, were observed hovering over the College Park area of Maryland by an Air Force member on duty in the control tower at Bolling Air Force Base in Washington, D.C. on July 28, 1954.
interesting points: The lower object was much brighter than the upper one.
As one of the objects disappeared, another object that looked like stars but was much lower and larger than any of the stars in the sky that night was observed.
The observer was unable to take more pictures due to a camera malfunction.
The observer described the speed of the objects as fast, and they appeared to be larger as they approached and then smaller as they gradually disappeared from view.
The observer had a star that was quite a bit larger and brighter than any star they had ever seen before, which was similar to the objects they observed.
sighted object: two brightly lit objects, one above the other
location: Bolling Air Force Base, Washington, D.C.
witnesses: Air Force member on duty in the control tower
photographs: no, the report states that the observer was unable to take more pictures due to a camera malfunction
